{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "eazyvtc-sprint4-orders",
    "name": "EazyVTC API — Sprint 4 — Bons de commande",
    "description": "# EazyVTC — Module Orders (Bons de commande)\n\n## Prérequis\n1. Importer cette collection **et** l'environnement `EazyVTC_Local`\n2. Avoir dans Supabase :\n   - Un compte `client@test.com` (rôle client)\n   - Un compte `driver@test.com` (rôle driver, statut active)\n   - Un compte `admin@test.com` (rôle admin)\n   - Un forfait tarifaire actif (country: france)\n3. Lancer l'API : `npm run dev`\n4. Créer le bucket Supabase Storage `orders-pdfs` (privé)\n\n## Ordre d'exécution\n1. **🔐 Setup — Tokens** : obtenir les 3 tokens\n2. **⚙️ Prérequis** : créer une réservation + assigner le chauffeur (déclenche la génération du bon)\n3. **📋 Lecture des bons** : tester toutes les routes GET\n4. **🔒 Contrôle d'accès** : vérifier les 401/403/404\n\n## Variables sauvegardées automatiquement\n- `client_token`, `driver_token`, `admin_token`\n- `reservation_id` — après création de la réservation\n- `order_id` — après récupération du bon\n- `flat_rate_id` — depuis la liste des forfaits",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",       "value": "http://localhost:4000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_token",   "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_token",   "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "admin_token",    "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "reservation_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "order_id",       "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "flat_rate_id",   "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_record_id","value": "", "type": "string", "description": "ID table public.drivers (pas users.id) — récupérer depuis Supabase ou via GET /admin/drivers" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "🔐 Setup — Tokens",
      "description": "Exécuter ces 3 requêtes en premier pour remplir client_token, driver_token et admin_token.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "Login Client",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{client_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{client_password}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('client_token sauvegardé', () => {",
                "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(json.data.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('client_token', json.data.access_token);",
                "  console.log('✅ client_token OK');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "Login Driver",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{driver_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{driver_password}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('driver_token sauvegardé', () => {",
                "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_token', json.data.access_token);",
                "  if (json.data.driver) {",
                "    pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_record_id', json.data.driver.id);",
                "    console.log('✅ driver_record_id sauvegardé:', json.data.driver.id);",
                "  }",
                "  console.log('✅ driver_token OK');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "Login Admin",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{admin_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{admin_password}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('admin_token sauvegardé', () => {",
                "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('admin_token', json.data.access_token);",
                "  console.log('✅ admin_token OK');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "⚙️ Prérequis — Créer et assigner une réservation",
      "description": "Ces deux requêtes déclenchent la génération automatique du bon de commande.\n1. Le client crée une réservation\n2. L'admin assigne un chauffeur → ordersService.createFromReservation() est appelé automatiquement",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "1. Récupérer un forfait actif (flat_rate_id)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/pricing/flat-rates?country=france&is_active=true&page=1&limit=5",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["pricing", "flat-rates"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "country",   "value": "france" },
                { "key": "is_active", "value": "true" },
                { "key": "page",      "value": "1" },
                { "key": "limit",     "value": "5" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('flat_rate_id sauvegardé', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  if (data.flat_rates.length > 0) {",
                "    pm.collectionVariables.set('flat_rate_id', data.flat_rates[0].id);",
                "    console.log('✅ flat_rate_id:', data.flat_rates[0].id, '— label:', data.flat_rates[0].label);",
                "  } else {",
                "    console.warn('⚠️ Aucun forfait actif en France — les tests suivants utiliseront la formule distance/durée');",
                "  }",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "2. [Client] Créer une réservation (forfait)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"pickup_address\": \"1 Avenue de Massy, 91300 Massy, France\",\n  \"pickup_lat\": 48.7253,\n  \"pickup_lng\": 2.2668,\n  \"dest_address\": \"Aéroport d'Orly, 94390 Orly, France\",\n  \"dest_lat\": 48.7262,\n  \"dest_lng\": 2.3652,\n  \"vehicle_type\": \"berline\",\n  \"country\": \"france\",\n  \"scheduled_at\": \"2026-06-15T09:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"comment\": \"Siège enfant requis\",\n  \"flat_rate_id\": \"{{flat_rate_id}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 201 — réservation créée', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                "pm.test('reservation_id sauvegardé', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(data.id).to.be.a('string');",
                "  pm.expect(data.status).to.equal('pending');",
                "  pm.expect(data.pricing_type).to.equal('flat_rate');",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('reservation_id', data.id);",
                "  console.log('✅ reservation_id:', data.id);",
                "  console.log('   Prix estimé:', data.price_estimated, 'EUR');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "2b. [Client] Créer une réservation (formule — fallback si pas de forfait)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"pickup_address\": \"10 Rue de la Gare, 91300 Massy, France\",\n  \"dest_address\": \"Aéroport CDG, Terminal 2, 95700 Roissy-en-France\",\n  \"vehicle_type\": \"berline\",\n  \"country\": \"france\",\n  \"scheduled_at\": \"2026-06-15T10:30:00.000Z\",\n  \"comment\": \"Vol AF123 — arriver 2h avant\",\n  \"distance_km\": 35,\n  \"duration_min\": 55\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "const flatRateId = pm.collectionVariables.get('flat_rate_id');",
                "if (flatRateId) {",
                "  console.log('ℹ️ flat_rate_id déjà défini — cette requête est un fallback, pas besoin de l\\'exécuter');",
                "  return;",
                "}",
                "pm.test('Status 201 — réservation formule créée (fallback)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                "const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "if (ok) {",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('reservation_id', data.id);",
                "  console.log('✅ reservation_id (formule):', data.id);",
                "  console.log('   Prix estimé:', data.price_estimated, 'EUR');",
                "}"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "3. [Admin] Assigner le chauffeur → génère le bon automatiquement",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/assign",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "assign"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"driver_id\": \"{{driver_record_id}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200 — chauffeur assigné', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('Statut réservation = assigned', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(data.status).to.equal('assigned');",
                "  pm.expect(data.driver_id).to.be.a('string');",
                "  console.log('✅ Chauffeur assigné — bon de commande en cours de génération (async)');",
                "  console.log('   reservation_id:', data.id);",
                "  console.log('   driver_id:', data.driver_id);",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "4. [Admin] Vérifier que le bon a été généré (attente ~1s)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/orders/by-reservation/{{reservation_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["orders", "by-reservation", "{{reservation_id}}"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Petite pause pour laisser le temps au service async de créer le bon",
                  "const delay = ms => new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));",
                  "await delay(1500);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 — bon trouvé', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Structure du bon de commande valide', () => {",
                  "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                  "  pm.expect(data.id).to.be.a('string');",
                  "  pm.expect(data.order_number).to.match(/^BC-\\d{4}-\\d{6}$/);",
                  "  pm.expect(data.reservation_id).to.equal(pm.collectionVariables.get('reservation_id'));",
                  "  pm.expect(data.driver_snapshot).to.include.keys(['first_name','last_name','phone','siret']);",
                  "  pm.expect(data.passenger_snapshot).to.include.keys(['first_name','last_name','phone']);",
                  "  pm.expect(data.trip_snapshot).to.include.keys(['pickup_address','dest_address','vehicle_type','scheduled_at','via','pricing_type','currency']);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('order_id', data.id);",
                  "  console.log('✅ order_id sauvegardé:', data.id);",
                  "  console.log('   Numéro bon:', data.order_number);",
                  "  console.log('   pricing_type:', data.trip_snapshot.pricing_type);",
                  "  console.log('   final_price dans snapshot:', data.trip_snapshot.final_price, '(null si formule — CDC p.26)');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('CDC p.26 — formule : final_price null dans le snapshot', () => {",
                  "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (data.trip_snapshot.pricing_type === 'formula') {",
                  "    pm.expect(data.trip_snapshot.final_price).to.be.null;",
                  "    console.log('✅ Règle CDC respectée : pas de montant pour la formule');",
                  "  } else {",
                  "    pm.expect(data.trip_snapshot.final_price).to.be.a('number').and.greaterThan(0);",
                  "    console.log('✅ Forfait : montant affiché =', data.trip_snapshot.final_price, data.trip_snapshot.currency);",
                  "  }",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "📋 Lecture des bons",
      "description": "Tester toutes les routes GET du module orders avec les 3 rôles.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "📂 Admin — Vue globale",
          "item": [

            {
              "name": "[Admin] Liste tous les bons (paginée)",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/orders?page=1&limit=10",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["orders"],
                  "query": [
                    { "key": "page",  "value": "1" },
                    { "key": "limit", "value": "10" }
                  ]
                }
              },
              "event": [{
                "listen": "test",
                "script": {
                  "exec": [
                    "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                    "pm.test('Structure pagination valide', () => {",
                    "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                    "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                    "  pm.expect(data).to.include.keys(['orders','total','page','limit','total_pages']);",
                    "  pm.expect(data.orders).to.be.an('array');",
                    "  pm.expect(data.page).to.equal(1);",
                    "  pm.expect(data.limit).to.equal(10);",
                    "  console.log('Total bons en base:', data.total);",
                    "});"
                  ]
                }
              }]
            },

            {
              "name": "[Admin] Liste filtrée par reservation_id",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/orders?reservation_id={{reservation_id}}",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["orders"],
                  "query": [{ "key": "reservation_id", "value": "{{reservation_id}}" }]
                }
              },
              "event": [{
                "listen": "test",
                "script": {
                  "exec": [
                    "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                    "pm.test('Filtre reservation_id respecté', () => {",
                    "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
                    "  pm.expect(data.total).to.be.at.least(1);",
                    "  if (data.orders.length > 0) {",
                    "    pm.expect(data.orders[0].reservation_id).to.equal(pm.collectionVariables.get('reservation_id'));",
                    "  }",
                    "});"
                  ]
                }
              }]
            },

            {
              "name": "[Admin] Détail d'un bon par ID",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/orders/{{order_id}}",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["orders", "{{order_id}}"]
                }
              },
              "event": [{
                "listen": "test",
                "script": {
                  "exec": [
                    "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                    "pm.test('Bon complet retourné', () => {",
                    "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                    "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                    "  pm.expect(data.id).to.equal(pm.collectionVariables.get('order_id'));",
                    "  pm.expect(data.order_number).to.match(/^BC-\\d{4}-\\d{6}$/);",
                    "  pm.expect(data.issued_at).to.be.a('string');",
                    "  pm.expect(data.driver_snapshot.first_name).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                    "  pm.expect(data.passenger_snapshot.first_name).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                    "});"
                  ]
                }
              }]
            },

            {
              "name": "[Admin] Bon par reservation_id",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/orders/by-reservation/{{reservation_id}}",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["orders", "by-reservation", "{{reservation_id}}"]
                }
              },
              "event": [{
                "listen": "test",
                "script": {
                  "exec": [
                    "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                    "pm.test('reservation_id cohérent', () => {",
                    "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
                    "  pm.expect(data.reservation_id).to.equal(pm.collectionVariables.get('reservation_id'));",
                    "});"
                  ]
                }
              }]
            },

            {
              "name": "[Admin] PDF — Redirection 302 vers URL signée",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/orders/{{order_id}}/pdf",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["orders", "{{order_id}}", "pdf"]
                }
              },
              "event": [{
                "listen": "test",
                "script": {
                  "exec": [
                    "pm.test('Status 302 (redirect) ou 200 (si Postman suit les redirections)', () => {",
                    "  // Postman suit les redirections par défaut → peut arriver à 200 (le PDF)",
                    "  // ou 302 si le suivi est désactivé",
                    "  const status = pm.response.code;",
                    "  pm.expect([200, 302]).to.include(status);",
                    "  console.log('Status reçu:', status);",
                    "  if (status === 200) {",
                    "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('application/pdf');",
                    "    console.log('✅ PDF reçu directement (redirect suivi par Postman)');",
                    "  } else {",
                    "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Location')).to.be.a('string').and.include('supabase');",
                    "    console.log('✅ Redirection vers URL signée Supabase Storage');",
                    "  }",
                    "});"
                  ]
                }
              }]
            }

          ]
        },

        {
          "name": "📂 Client — Ses propres bons",
          "item": [

            {
              "name": "[Client] Liste de ses bons (/mine)",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/orders/mine?page=1&limit=10",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["orders", "mine"],
                  "query": [
                    { "key": "page",  "value": "1" },
                    { "key": "limit", "value": "10" }
                  ]
                }
              },
              "event": [{
                "listen": "test",
                "script": {
                  "exec": [
                    "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                    "pm.test('Client voit uniquement ses propres bons', () => {",
                    "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                    "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                    "  pm.expect(data).to.include.keys(['orders','total','page','limit','total_pages']);",
                    "  pm.expect(data.orders).to.be.an('array');",
                    "  pm.expect(data.total).to.be.at.least(1);",
                    "  // Vérifier qu'aucun champ jointure interne n'est exposé",
                    "  if (data.orders.length > 0) {",
                    "    pm.expect(data.orders[0]).to.not.have.property('reservation.client_id');",
                    "  }",
                    "  console.log('Bons du client:', data.total);",
                    "});"
                  ]
                }
              }]
            },

            {
              "name": "[Client] Détail de son bon",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/orders/{{order_id}}",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["orders", "{{order_id}}"]
                }
              },
              "event": [{
                "listen": "test",
                "script": {
                  "exec": [
                    "pm.test('Status 200 — client accède à son propre bon', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                    "pm.test('Snapshots corrects', () => {",
                    "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
                    "  pm.expect(data.driver_snapshot).to.include.keys(['first_name','last_name']);",
                    "  pm.expect(data.passenger_snapshot).to.include.keys(['first_name','last_name']);",
                    "  pm.expect(data.trip_snapshot.via).to.equal('EazyVTC');",
